<HEADLINE>
FT  27 JUL 94 / UK Company News: Equifax in Pounds 39m purchase
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Equifax, the Atlanta-based information services group, and UAPT-Infolink,
the United Kingdom credit referencing business, last night announced a
recommended all-cash offer for UAPT-Infolink.
The offer, at Pounds 5 per share, values UAPT-Infolink at approximately
Pounds 39m.
It represents a premium of 49.3 per cent over the UAPT-Infolink share price
of Pounds 3.35 on July 25, 1994.
The board of UAPT-Infolink is unanimously recommending the offer.
Equifax has received undertakings to accept or indications of support in
relation to the offer in respect of 32.1 per cent of UAPT-Infolink's issued
ordinary share capital.
Mr Travis Halford, chief executive of Equifax Europe, commenting on the
offer, said last night: 'We are delighted to have agreed terms with
UAPT-Infolink's board. This attractive offer for UAPT-Infolink is made
possible by virtue of the efficiencies our combined UK businesses can
achieve.'
</TEXT>
