<HEADLINE>
FT  26 JUL 94 / International Company News: French group proposes merger
with Stena arm
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID LASCELLES, Resources Editor
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LONDON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Coflexip, the French manufacturer of flexible pipe for the offshore oil
industry, has proposed a merger with Stena Offshore, the sub-sea contracting
arm of Stena of Sweden. The Dollars 230m transaction will create a sub-sea
oilfield products and services group with sales of Dollars 650m.
Coflexip, whose biggest shareholders include Elf Aquitaine, will finance the
deal through a combination of securities and Dollars 30m in cash.
Mr Christian Marbach, Coflexip's chairman, said Stena's strengths in
offshore contracting made the merger a good match. Coflexip's skill,
meanwhile, was in manufacturing and technology.
