FT  26 JUL 94 / World Trade News: Move to extend Israeli deals
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NANCY DUNNE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Richard Gephardt, the US House majority leader, and 28 other House
members are proposing an expansion of the US-Israel free trade agreement to
include countries which sign comprehensive peace accords with Israel, Nancy
Dunne writes from Washington.
The proposal is supported by many Democrats who have been prominent on both
sides of trade debates.
The US and Israel signed a free trade pact in 1985, spurring an increase in
trade between the two countries. 'Expanding this agreement will require the
US and Israel to negotiate with each new party for reciprocal elimination of
trade barriers,' Mr Gephardt said.
